  "prompt": "What is the best Call Of Duty?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" Call of Duty game is subjective and often depends on personal preference, as each entry in the series has its own strengths and unique features. However, a few titles are widely regarded as standouts in the franchise:\n\n1. **Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare (2007)**  \n   - Often considered a revolutionary game in the series, it introduced modern-day combat and set the standard for first-person shooters. Its campaign and multiplayer are still highly praised.\n\n2. **Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2 (2009)**  \n   - Built on the success of its predecessor, this game expanded the multiplayer experience with new maps, weapons, and mechanics like killstreaks. The campaign is also iconic.\n\n3. **Call of Duty: Black Ops (2010)**  \n   - Known for its gripping Cold War-era campaignand innovative Zombies mode, Black Ops brought a fresh narrative and gameplay style to the series. Its multiplayer was also highly popular.\n\n4. **Call of Duty: Warzone (2020)**  \n   - While not a traditional mainline game, Warzone redefined the franchise with its free-to-play battle royale mode, attracting millions of players worldwide.\n\n5. **Call of Duty: Modern Warfare (2019)**  \n   - A reboot of the original Modern Warfare, this game was praised for its realistic graphics, tight gameplay, and robust multiplayer experience.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" Call of Duty depends on what you value most\u2014campaign storytelling, multiplayer innovation, or other features. Let me know your preferences, and I can help narrow it down!",
